### Jira URL Functions - Test Requests

### Analyze Jira URL
POST http://localhost:3000/api/jira/analyze-url
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "url": "https://your-jira.atlassian.net/browse/PROJ-123"
}

### Create Task from Jira URL (with AI)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/jira/create-from-url
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "url": "https://your-jira.atlassian.net/browse/PROJ-123",
  "assignee": "user@example.com",
  "additionalInfo": "Дополнительная информация для новой задачи",
  "useAI": true
}

### Create Task from Jira URL (without AI)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/jira/create-from-url
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "url": "https://your-jira.atlassian.net/browse/PROJ-123",
  "assignee": "user@example.com",
  "additionalInfo": "Простая задача без AI",
  "useAI": false
}

### Clone Task
POST http://localhost:3000/api/jira/clone-task
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sourceUrl": "https://your-jira.atlassian.net/browse/PROJ-123",
  "targetProject": "NEWPROJ",
  "targetIssueType": "Task",
  "assignee": "user@example.com",
  "additionalInfo": "Клонированная задача с дополнительной информацией"
}

